<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4321] NIO+SSL Connector corrupts stream when data size exceeds SSL buffer size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4321</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the default enabledCipherSuites settings on Java 7, the NIO+SSL connector corrupts the SSL output stream when asked to flush a buffer larger than the SSL buffer size (approx. 16 KB). This is reproducible by sending a single BytesMessage &amp;gt;= 16KB to the broker and attempting to consume it. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;JDK 1.7.0_09, Windows 7 x64, Linux CentOS5 64-bit&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
